subSubSection.paragraph:
Genitalia
(
Figs. 70–73
) 1910 µm long. Ovipositor lobes large, rounded, densely clothed with short, modified setae (‘peg setae’); area between ovipositor lobes wide, with some short setae, tiny papillae, and a larger papilla caudally. Second pair of lobes, lateral and anterior to the ovipositor lobes, 3–4 times smaller than ovipositor lobes, but bearing very long, slender lamellar setae. Anterior apophyses distinctly shorter than posterior apophyses; prela (
Fig. 73
) comprised of three pairs of projections; one of these pairs form a large, angular, plate-like thickening (
Fig. 71
). Corpus bursae long and slender, without pectinations or signum. Accessory sac absent. Ductus spermathecae slender, very short, with two large coils (
Fig. 70
).
